thread.title: Alcoa’s News Isn’t All Bad for China
thread.title_full: Alcoa’s News Isn’t All Bad for China - WSJ

author: Abheek Bhattacharya
title: Alcoa’s News Isn’t All Bad for China
text:
Global raw-material producers have reason to fret about all the industries slowing down in China. But in the case of the Chinese auto industry, their fretting might actually point to some good news.
On Thursday, U.S. aluminum giant Alcoa lowered its estimates for growth in Chinese car production—to between 1% and 2% from a previous forecast of 5% to 8%. Partly, this is because car makers don’t see much consumer demand growth ahead....
